        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 31 at 5:40PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 540 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Elberon, or near Surry, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Smithfield around 555 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Rushmere, Booth Fork,
Pons, Carrollton, Benns Church, Bethel Church, Ellis Fork, Delk
Crossroads, Lawson, and Bacons Castle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
